# Cloudflare Pages redirects. Docusaurus copies static/* to the build root,
# and CF Pages honours a top-level _redirects file.
#
# /api was a dead path (404). The Intent API reference lives at /intent-api.
/api      /intent-api   301
/api/     /intent-api   301

# /institutional and /brand are NOT docs pages. Google indexed stale
# docs.ophis.fi/{institutional,brand} URLs from old links and flagged them 404
# (GSC, 2026-06). 301 them to the real destinations. CF Pages treats /x and /x/
# as distinct sources, so cover both forms (like /api above).
#
# /institutional: the swap route redirects to business.ophis.fi anyway
# (RoutesApp InstitutionalRedirect -> window.location), so point crawlers
# straight at the crawlable business host instead of the SPA shell.
/institutional    https://business.ophis.fi       301
/institutional/   https://business.ophis.fi       301
# /brand: a real swap-app HashRouter page (#/brand); no crawlable equivalent.
# Worst case CF drops the fragment and it lands on the live swap home (never 404).
/brand            https://swap.ophis.fi/#/brand   301
/brand/           https://swap.ophis.fi/#/brand   301
